Description: DNLI_BPT4 - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. DNA ligase, which is expressed in the early stage of lytic development, has been implicated in T4 DNA synthesis and genetic recombination. It may also play a role in T4 DNA repair. From Enterobacteria phage T4 (Bacteriophage T4).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
